<p>(I ought to have begun by thanking you for your kind letter:<ref target="#foot.f4"/> but I wanted to make sure of <hi rend="underline">Gasteria</hi>.—</p>
<p>Perhaps I ought to refrain from troubling you with this but I cannot help thinking that you will be interested with the plain evidence, without comment.)</p>
<p>You kindly offered to lend me the paper you mentioned opposing my views—<ref target="#foot.f5"/> I should be much obliged if you would kindly do so, and I would return it as soon as possible. At present I am inspecting vaccination in Herefordshire,<ref target="#foot.f6"/> but hope to get home about a week before Christmas.</p>
<p>Thank you for your hints about bud-dissection— I long for leisure to do that and more.</p>
<p>I am, my dear Sir, | Yours very sincerely | Hubert Airy <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/></p>
<p>Charles Darwin Esq. M.A., F.R.S. | Down, Kent.</p> 
